docs.text: sure , it's been used over and over , but for some reason , it is always fun to watch .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this cliche pretty much describes the level kiss the girls works on : overused , but always fun .

docs.text: one of my personal rules about watching a film is not how original the film is , but how it goes around giving its story .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this rule applies highly to kiss the girls .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is something psychologically stimulating in a well-crafted serial killer movie , and kiss the girls is certainly well made .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , the whole film screams of unoriginality , and so it relies on the power of its actors and the technical detail to pull it through .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: well , not only are the actors capable of pulling it through , but they add so much to the film that nearly every flaw is covered up .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unfortunately , one of the most revealing and rather insulting choices by the filmmakers ( one that seven , a film a lot like this one , knew not to make ) was to put the name of the killer in the opening credits .

docs.text: that may give the actor credit for the role , but throughout the film , hidden in my mind , i was waiting for him to appear on screen , which spoiled the mystery .

docs.text: plotwise , kiss the girls shows almost no originality .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we are introduced to detective alex cross ( morgan freeman ) , a forensic psychologist , and immediately we are given the cliched scene establishing him as the hero .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he gets a call about a woman who has shot her husband and is now threatening to kill herself .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: obviously cross succeeds at getting the gun , but this scene is quickly forgotten during the next scene .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: at his house , cross is told that his neice , naomi ( gina ravera ) , has been missing for four days .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this provides the motivation for cross to find the killer , but we are never given a chance to establish the relationship between the two , and as a result , we can't sympathize with detective cross .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , what makes kiss the girls slightly original is the introduction of one of the abductees . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: before she is abducted .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: dr . kate mctiernan ( ashley judd , the actress of the judd family ) is a smart , athletic woman , and because of these traits , becomes a target for casanova--what the serial killer likes to call himself .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: because of these character-developing scenes , we care for mctiernan , making the abduction scene all that more suspenseful .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after being abducted , mctiernan wakes up and finds herself in a cell somewhere in the woods .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: remembering that the killer gave her certain rules , she decides to break one of them by calling out .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when casanova comes to punish her , she breaks out and escapes by jumping over a waterfall .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after she is found , she begins to help cross find his neice .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: from this moment on , kiss the girls takes on the form of every other serial killer film , as the two leads search for the rest of the victims held captive .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: many people will compare this film to 1995's seven , another killer film starring morgan freeman , but i presume that the similarities are intentional .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the screenplay , by david klass , is adapted from the novel written by james patterson , and yet i don't quite see how this story could have worked in novel form .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: what makes kiss the girls so good is the acting and the technical and visual impressiveness .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the cinematography , by aaron schneider , is reminiscient of seven , and sometimes i felt that many of the shots were trying too hard to impress us .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sometimes a simple shot is the best one .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , many of the shots are stunning , and unlike seven , most of them take place during the day , in sunlight .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the scene when ashley judd is running through the forest is extremely well done , in more than one way .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the camera work is terrific , but the editing makes this scene work so well .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the chaotic and mtv-type cutting gives the audience a sense of confusion and unawareness , exactly what judd's character is experiencing .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , the best aspect of kiss the girls is its actors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: morgan freeman is one of today's most powerful and believable actors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: detective cross is a very good character for him , although it is just a similar one to the character in seven .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: because of freeman's powerful presence , he carries half the film by himself .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the other half is carried by ashley judd , one of today's most promising dramatic actresses .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in fact , her performance is better than freeman's , if that is even possible .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: her character is more original than freeman's , and she handles it wonderfully .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we finally have a female character in a movie like this who does more than just scream .

docs.text: the supporting cast is highly underdeveloped , but the cast members do as much as they can with it .

docs.text: cary elwes portrays a cop in north carolina , and unfortunately has scraps for a character .

docs.text: gina ravera gives a good performance , but again she isn't in many of the scenes .

docs.text: so as a result of all these small supporting parts , the weight of the film lies on the two leads , and they do a phenomenal job .
